Sentencas: Ba(Ce(0.8)Y(0.2))O(3-delta) anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cells were fabricated and tested.
Titulo: Tortuosity in anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cell found from current flow rates and dusty-gas model

Sentencas: By changing the H(2) partial pressure at the anode side, the effect of anodic concentration polarization on open-circuit voltage of the cell was observed.
Titulo: Tortuosity in anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cell found from current flow rates and dusty-gas model

Sentencas: Saturation current densities under concentration polarization were obtained from different anode thickness cells and were used for tortuosity calculation.
Titulo: Tortuosity in anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cell found from current flow rates and dusty-gas model

Sentencas: The calculation is based on the dusty-gas model which includes Knudsen diffusion and Stefan-Maxwell equation terms.
Titulo: Tortuosity in anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cell found from current flow rates and dusty-gas model

Sentencas: The tortuosity value for our supporting anode is 1.55 +/- 0.1 which is in a physically reasonable range for modern porous anode materials.
Titulo: Tortuosity in anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cell found from current flow rates and dusty-gas model

Sentencas: The tortuosity that we found is independent of the cell testing temperature and anode thickness, which is consistent with the fact that tortuosity is a geometric factor of the anode structure.
Titulo: Tortuosity in anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cell found from current flow rates and dusty-gas model

Sentencas: The derived equation also can be used for predicting the effect of varying the anode thickness, porosity and pore size.
Titulo: Tortuosity in anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cell found from current flow rates and dusty-gas model

Sentencas: Also, the concentration of the gases as a function of position across the anode is determined.
Titulo: Tortuosity in anode-supported proton conductive solid oxide fuel cell found from current flow rates and dusty-gas model
